1361
01:57:18,833 --> 01:57:24,292
<i>♪ Now's the day, and now's the hour ♪</i>

1362
01:57:24,750 --> 01:57:30,500
<i>♪ See the front of battle lour ♪</i>

1363
01:57:30,708 --> 01:57:36,042
<i>♪ See approach proud Edward's power ♪</i>

1364
01:57:36,333 --> 01:57:40,458
<i>♪ Chains and slavery ♪</i>

1365
01:57:42,375 --> 01:57:47,292
<i>♪ Wha will be a traitor knave? ♪</i>

1366
01:57:48,167 --> 01:57:53,542
<i>♪ Wha can fill a coward's grave? ♪</i>

1367
01:57:53,875 --> 01:57:59,417
<i>♪ Wha sae base as be a slave? ♪</i>

1368
01:57:59,583 --> 01:58:03,542
<i>♪ Let him turn and flee! ♪</i>

1369
01:58:05,375 --> 01:58:10,625
<i>♪ Wha for Scotland's king and law ♪</i>

1370
01:58:11,000 --> 01:58:16,625
<i>♪ Freedom's sword will strongly draw ♪</i>

1371
01:58:16,833 --> 01:58:22,500
<i>♪ Free-man stand, or free-man fa' ♪</i>

1372
01:58:22,792 --> 01:58:26,875
<i>♪ Let him follow me! ♪</i>

1373
01:58:28,458 --> 01:58:33,750
<i>♪ By oppression's woes and pain! ♪</i>

